summary:
CALIBRE Systems Inc., an employee-owned Management Consulting and Information Technology Services company is looking for a driven, detail-oriented Web Developer to work within a larger team to lead design and development efforts to implement the best solutions for end users based on product capabilities and customer needs. The Web Developer will work within teams to assist in designing and then implementing a blend of HTML, CSS and JavaScript to code the designs. Specific responsibilities include, but are not limited to:

Utilize JQuery, Javascript, .NET (C#), HTML programming expertise to develop, deploy, and maintain applications;
Ability to develop in ECM environment, such as Open Text, Documentum or SharePoint.
Develop custom power views, electronic forms, workflow scripts, helper applications, migration utilities
Write and troubleshoot SQL scripts;
Translate UI/UX wireframes to visual elements.
Analyze code and provide recommendations for improvements based on best practices;
Contribute to all stages of application development, from UI design to final testing;
Ability to work closely with other developers to implement solutions to support planned functionality;
Motivated and can complete assigned tasks related to projects and technical requests;
Required Skills
Must be able to obtain a Public Trust Clearance;
Strong software engineering expertise, object-oriented programming, source code control, unit testing, re-usable code, security, enterprise systems, and scaling;
Has developed a broad perspective by holding several IT assignments with exposure to multiple IT, knowledge management, and business areas;
Able to work in a team as a leader or member with a focus on exceeding customer expectations;
Ability to work in a fast-paced environment with changing priorities;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Ability to accomplish task within a given timeline with minimal supervision;
Able to work independently, under general supervision and as a part of a team, on several concurrent tasks with changing priorities;
Take control in resolving issues/defect in timely manner and innovative to propose solutions to complex problems
Required Experience
Bachelor's degree in software engineering or computer science or equivalent experience;
Experience working in Content Management software, such as Open Text Content Server;
Experience in planning and delivering software platforms used across multiple products and organizational units.
Deep expertise and hands on experience with Web Applications and programming languages such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JQuery and API's.
Deep functional knowledge or hands on design experience with Web Services (REST, SOAP, etc.)
Experience writing and tuning stored procedures, triggers, functions and views in SQL Server.
CALIBRE is an Equal Opportunity Employer and supports transitioning service members, veterans and individuals with disabilities. We offer a competitive salary and full benefits package. To be considered, please apply via our website at www.calibresys.com. Come join our dynamic team!


#CALIBREcareers


Job Location
Rockville, Maryland, United States
Position Type
Full-Time/Regular

We are looking for an outstanding web developer to be responsible for the coding and maintenance of IJM Canada’s website and online donation platforms, which includes online giving, peer-to-peer fundraising, and gift catalogue.


Responsibilities


Lead the development and maintenance of the IJM Canada website, with a focus on user interface and user experience, and converting online leads to online donations. This includes, but is not limited to:

Create sitemaps, screen flows, and webpages;
Provide guidance for wireframes;
Optimize website for mobile;
Implement SEO, Google Analytics, and Google Campaigns;
On an ongoing basis, conduct usability testing to ensure an exceptional experience for back-end users and front-end consumers; and
Trouble-shoot and solve weaknesses in website CMS.
Create, maintain and consistently improve the technological capabilities of IJM Canada’s current online giving platforms: online donation, peer-to-peer fundraising, and gift catalogue. This includes, but is not limited to:

Integrate online giving platforms with IJM Canada website;
Trouble-shoot and fix issues for all giving platforms; and
Optimize user interface for all giving platforms.
Other

Manage accessibility requirements for website and other available content.
Ensure seamless integration of marketing automation platform with IJM Canada website and database (IE – MailChimp, etc.).
Work cross-departmentally to ensure integration of team needs across all platforms.
Required Skills and Experience

BSc or Diploma in Computer Science, Web Development, or related field;
1 to 2 years relevant work experience (experience acquired through internships will be considered);
Strong working knowledge of programming languages such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript and APIs;
Proven ability to optimize web experiences for mobile;
Proven ability to work with marketing automation platforms such as MailChimp;
Proven ability to implement Google Analytics, Google Campaigns, SEO and new, emerging data generation tools;
Experience with Web User Interface (UI)/ User Experience (UX) Design;
Experience integrating data from various back-end services and databases such as Blackbaud and Salesforce;
Proven ability leading successful web development projects; and
Proven ability with implementation and management of online giving platforms (IE.Salesforce, Blackbaud/NetCommunity).
Critical Qualities

Humble and resilient;
Pursues excellence;
Culturally aware and appreciative of differences;
Strong service ethic;
Innovative problem solver;
Ability to build trust and strong partnerships with others;
Courageous in pursuing opportunities and challenges;
Tenacious in achieving goals; and
Professional.
Organization Information

IJM Canada offers a competitive salary, with medical, dental and retirement benefits.
Position reports to the Manager of Marketing & Communications.
Position based at IJM Canada headquarters in London, Ontario.
Applications accepted until the position is filled – target start date December 2017.

Submit Resume, Cover Letter & Statement of Faith* in one document to applications@ijm.ca


*What is a statement of faith?

A statement of faith should describe your Christian faith and how you see it as relevant to your involvement with IJM. The statement can either be incorporated into the cover letter or submitted as a separate document and should include, at a minimum, a description of your spiritual disciplines (prayer, study, etc.) and your current fellowship or place of worship.
